					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A kabbalistic work of Menahem Azariah da Fano.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="12v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tefilot ṿe-seder teḳi῾ot le-yamim nora᾿im ῾im kaṿanot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תפלות וסדר תקיעות לימים נוראים עם כונות </title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/23282531">Fano, Menahem Azariah da 1548-1620</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/23282531">מנחם עזריה, מפאנו</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>A treatise on the shofar blasts of Menahem Azariah da Fano, followed by kabbalistic notes on other portions of the services for the New Year's feast and the Day of Atonement.</p>
								<p>On folio 11r begins a part dealing with the custom of 'tashlikh': "נוהגים באשכנז לילך ביום א' של ר"ה אחר תפלת המנחה אל הים".</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>12 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>210</height>
										<width>155</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>150</height>
										<width>100</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>12 folios (+ 5 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 27 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of 6 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="26" writtenLines="26">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Initial words in large characters, divine names in larger square characters.</p>
									<p>Comments and notes in the margin, in small cursive and semi-cursive.</p>
									<p>Folio 2 is a title page, with a printed (engraved) design.</p>
									<p>Watermark of a crwoned cross within a coat of arms held by two griffins, with initials MR, folio [13] (first end flyleaf).</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script of the 17th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 1v: a short description of the manuscript in English.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Card with dark brown leather corners and spine.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Sod Hathekioth. Hebr. Mus. Brit. Jure Empt. 18,228.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
